Alfred Kammer, Director, European Department, International Monetary Fund, Jan Švejnar, Director, Center on Global Economy and Governance, School of International and Public Affairs, Columbia University, Paula Pinho, Director for Just Transition, Consumers, Energy Efficiency and Innovation, Directorate-General for Energy, European Commission and Olga Khakova, Deputy Director, European Energy Security, Atlantic Council with the moderator Karen Tso discussed how the energy crisis has affected CESEE economies.